reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2020
reviews.reviewText: The only thing I wasn't sure about was there wasn't any way to put them on my steam cleaner. No velcro or ties. I will probably sew some on myself with old shoe strings or some such. They will work just fine after that. I have no issue with the quality or workmanship. Would return if I couldn't use them. It must have been different machine that these were for. The Thane H2O machine I have is an inherited one from the people we purchased our house from, so no way of knowing which ones to order. Thought they would have had some kind of way to attach to the bottom of the machine. I got some others that had ties, so these kind of surprised me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2022
reviews.reviewText: After owning the green H20 steamer for many years I never knew there these thick blue pads could be used for my version, but I took a chance purchasing them thinking I'd have to make them work on my machine somehow but to my surprise they were the exact shape of the original white pads with the same velcro design! They fit my machine perfect and so much more absorbent than the originals, they work excellent on my hardwood floors and even better on my area carpets!! Love them and got them for an excellent price, great value!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 9, 2019
reviews.reviewText: I really like these chenille mop heads. I would use them all the time except for the velcro does not stay on thebottom like they do on the white ones. They are easy to clean, but don't last as long. I am hoping they willimprove the velcro sometime.

You will have to do it separately the old fashioned way.
